column2: Old Xerox Experimental values. Invalid as an Ethertype since 1983.
Formerly XEROX PUP. Invalid as an Ethertype since 1983. Use 0x0A00.
Formerly PUP Addr Trans. Invalid as an Ethertype since 1983. Use 0x0A01.
Old Nixdorf private protocol. Invalid as an Ethertype since 1983.
Customer VLAN Tag Type (C-Tag, formerly called the Q-Tag) (initially Wellfleet)
IEEE Std 802.3 - Ethernet Passive Optical Network (EPON)
Ethernet NIC hardware and software testing
IEEE Std 802.1X - Port-based network access control
IEEE Std 802.1Q - Service VLAN tag identifier (S-Tag)
IEEE Std 802.1AB - Link Layer Discovery Protocol (LLDP)
IEEE Std 802.1AE - Media Access Control Security
IEEE Std 802.1Q  - Multiple VLAN Registration Protocol (MVRP)
IEEE Std 802.1Q - Multiple Multicast Registration Protocol (MMRP)
IEEE Std 802.11 - Fast Roaming Remote Request (802.11r)
IEEE Std 802.21 - Media Independent Handover Protocol
IEEE Std 802.1Qbe - Multiple I-SID Registration Protocol
IEEE Std 802.1Qbg - ECP Protocol (also used in 802.1BR)
GeoNetworking as defined in ETSI EN 302 636-4-1

The Ethertype will be used to identify a "Channel" in which control messages are encapsulated as payload of GRE packets. When a GRE packet tagged with the Ethertype is received, the payload will be handed to the network processor for processing.
